org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.matchers.psystem.queries

Interface PQuery

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    InitializablePQuery, IQuerySpecification<Matcher>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseGeneratedQuerySpecification, BaseQuerySpecification, GenericQuerySpecification

    public interface PQuery
    A definition of queries usable inside pattern descriptions. Such description always has (a non-null) name. The query itself is defined as a (non-empty) set of PBody instances, the result is the disjunction of the single PBody instances.

    A PQuery might be constructed from erroneous patterns or might be uninitialized - this is represented by its status.

    Since:
    0.8.0
    Author:
    Zoltan Ujhelyi
